The paper deals with the analysis of a hashing scheme, which is a common topic in the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of statistical physics methods to determine the load thresholds suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and possibly also to statistical inference (cs.SI). The mention of an algorithm for constructing placements in linear time suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the use of graph limits and belief propagation equations suggests a connection to probability and statistics (cs.PF).
